# Build after extension changes

This repo is a browser extension. **Source lives under `src/`.** Edits are not loaded in the browser until you stage a build.

## Required step

After **any** change to extension code, locales, or manifests, run:

```bash
node scripts/build.mjs
```

From the repo root. This validates locales, syncs background modules, and writes:

- `build/staging-firefox/` — load unpacked in Firefox (`about:debugging`)
- `build/staging-chrome/` — load unpacked in Chrome (`chrome://extensions`)

Do this **before** telling the user to reload or test the extension. Do not skip because the last turn already built — rebuild if new edits were made in this session.

## When to run

- After editing files under `src/` (`.js`, `.html`, `_locales/**`, manifests, platform entrypoints)
- After adding/removing files listed in `scripts/build.mjs` `SHARED_FILES`
- At the end of a multi-file task, once all edits are done (not after every single file mid-task)

## Optional targets

```bash
node scripts/build.mjs firefox   # Firefox only
node scripts/build.mjs chrome    # Chrome only
node scripts/build.mjs clean     # remove build/
```

## If build fails

Fix locale key mismatches or `background-modules.firefox.json` / `background-sw.chrome.js` drift before finishing the task.
